<item>
            <title>[POOL-162] When waiting threads are interrupted, pool can leak capacity</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/POOL-162</link>
                <project id="12310488" key="POOL">Commons Pool</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As reported on commons-dev (&lt;a href=&quot;http://markmail.org/message/aqb23nnzyy2ar3vs&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://markmail.org/message/aqb23nnzyy2ar3vs&lt;/a&gt;), when waiting threads are interrupted, GOP, GKOP may leak capacity.   I do not yet have a test case to confirm this, but I suspect that the problem reported by the user is caused by a missing  _allocationQueue.remove(latch) before rethrowing InterruptedException in borrowObject.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
